df['month'] = [int(i.split('.')[1]) for i in df['date']]
df['year'] = [int(i.split('.')[2]) for i in df['date']]

In [11]:
df_4 = df.groupby(['hour', 'month']).mean().reset_index()[['hour', 'month', 'CONSUMPTION']]
months = np.array([0, 'January', 'February', 'March', 'April', 'May', 'June', 'July', 'August', 'September', 'October', 'November', 'December'])

def season(month):
    ind = months.tolist().index(month)
    if ind < 3 or ind == 12:
        return "Winter"
    if ind >=3 and ind < 6:
        return "Spring"
    if ind >=6 and ind < 9:
        return "Summer"
    else:
        return "Autumn"

def season_month(month):
    ind = months.tolist().index(month)
    return (ind)%3

df_4['month'] = months[df_4['month']]
df_4['season'] = [season(month) for month in df_4['month']]
df_4['season_month'] = [season_month(month) for month in df_4['month']]
In [12]:
df_5 = df.copy()
df_5['weekind'] = [datetime(y, m, d).weekday() for d, m, y in df_5.iloc[:, -3:].values]
df_5['weekday'] = [calendar.day_name[i] for i in df_5['weekind'] ]
df_5 = df_5.groupby('weekday').mean()[['CONSUMPTION', 'weekind']].reset_index().sort_values(by=['weekind'])
df_5['CONSUMPTION'] = [round(i) for i in df_5['CONSUMPTION']]

1. Power Generation Structure of Ukraine by years¶

In [13]:
import plotly.express as px

fig = px.area(df_1, x="year", y=['AES', 'TES', 'TEC', 'GES', 'VDE', 'GAES_GEN'], labels={"year": "Year", "variable": "Power Source", 'value': "Generation"}, template="plotly_dark")

fig.update_traces(textposition='top center', mode='lines+markers')

fig.update_layout(
    title = "Annual Generated Power by Source Type, MW",
    autosize=False,
    width=950,
    height=500,
    margin=dict(l=20, r=20, t=40, b=20),
    
    yaxis=dict(
        title_text="Power Generated",
        tickvals=[25e6, 50e6, 75e6, 100e6, 150e6, 125e6, 175e6],
        tickmode="array",
    ),
    
    legend=dict(
        traceorder="reversed",
    )
)

fig.update_yaxes(automargin=True, zeroline=False)
fig.update_xaxes(title_text='Year', zeroline=False)


fig.update_xaxes(showspikes=True, spikethickness=1, spikesnap="cursor", spikemode="across")
fig.update_yaxes(showspikes=True, spikethickness=1)

fig.show()
